when you blush.

722
01:05:15,124 --> 01:05:17,496
Like a wild flower.

723
01:05:17,543 --> 01:05:20,876
It's my dyspepsia.

724
01:05:22,548 --> 01:05:23,579
Morning, all.

725
01:05:25,134 --> 01:05:26,332
Beautiful day.

726
01:05:45,404 --> 01:05:47,147
Pack of Gitanes, please.

727
01:05:47,197 --> 01:05:51,112
Bravo! Vive la France! You scalded me.

728
01:05:51,159 --> 01:05:55,573
Bravo! Ten out of ten! Bull's-eye!

729
01:05:59,585 --> 01:06:01,744
It was Amélie. She...

730
01:06:35,746 --> 01:06:39,743
Do you know what happened
when they went up Mont Blanc?

731
01:06:39,791 --> 01:06:42,248
The silicon in her face froze up.

732
01:06:42,295 --> 01:06:46,791
Her face was a festering mass!

733
01:07:12,658 --> 01:07:16,442
Mulled wine and ginger biscuits.

734
01:07:17,496 --> 01:07:19,156
Thank you.

735
01:07:19,206 --> 01:07:22,409
I was too hard the other day
on the girl with the glass.

736
01:07:23,460 --> 01:07:27,411
Tell me about that boy she saw.
Did they meet again?

737
01:07:28,966 --> 01:07:29,998
No.

738
01:07:31,219 --> 01:07:32,878
They're into different things.

739
01:07:33,929 --> 01:07:36,503
Luck is like the Tour de France.

740
01:07:36,557 --> 01:07:38,633
You wait, and it flashes past you.

741
01:07:40,227 --> 01:07:44,177
You have to catch it while you can.

742
01:08:08,589 --> 01:08:10,333
Can I help you?

743
01:08:10,383 --> 01:08:13,550
Excuse me.
I found this album in the street and I...

744
01:08:13,594 --> 01:08:18,173
Nino will be so pleased!
He was so sad the other day.

745
01:08:18,224 --> 01:08:20,181
I almost prayed to St Anthony.

746
01:08:21,727 --> 01:08:23,933
Is... Nino there?

747
01:08:23,979 --> 01:08:26,766
No. On Wednesdays he works at the funfair.

748
01:08:29,109 --> 01:08:31,185
How long has he had this collection?

749
01:08:31,236 --> 01:08:35,698
Since I got him the job here, last year.

750
01:08:35,742 --> 01:08:39,953
Before, he collected footprints.
He worked nights.

751
01:08:39,996 --> 01:08:45,950
In the daytime
he took pictures of footprints in wet cement.

752
01:08:46,001 --> 01:08:48,160
He's a funny guy.

753
01:08:48,212 --> 01:08:50,501
When we met, he was a Santa Claus.

754
01:08:53,675 --> 01:08:55,420
Other things like...

755
01:08:55,470 --> 01:08:59,337
Whenever he heard a funny laugh, he'd tape it.

756
01:09:03,519 --> 01:09:04,550
Really?

757
01:09:06,397 --> 01:09:09,018
Must be hard for his girlfriend.

758
01:09:09,066 --> 01:09:11,391
He never keeps them long.

759
01:09:11,443 --> 01:09:14,230
Times are hard for dreamers.

760
01:09:14,279 --> 01:09:17,068
Eva! Where are those coffees?

761
01:09:17,117 --> 01:09:19,572
I'd better go. Thanks for the album.

762
01:09:19,619 --> 01:09:23,284
It's OK. I've got time to take it to the funfair.

763
01:09:23,331 --> 01:09:27,791
Suit yourself. The ghost train.
Ask for Nino Quincampoix, like the street.

764
01:09:52,068 --> 01:09:54,190
I'm looking for Nino. Is he here?

765
01:09:54,236 --> 01:09:56,312
