766
01:09:57,865 --> 01:10:00,272
- Is there no way to see him before?
- Sure.

767
01:10:01,618 --> 01:10:03,197
20 francs.

768
01:11:14,150 --> 01:11:15,775
See you next Wednesday.

769
01:11:27,455 --> 01:11:31,916
5pm tomorrow, Montmartre carousel
near the phone box. Bring a 5 franc piece.

770
01:11:50,019 --> 01:11:52,142
Want to know about her?

771
01:11:54,733 --> 01:11:57,603
- You know her? You saw her?
- You bet.

772
01:11:57,652 --> 01:11:59,645
She put us in her shirt pocket.

773
01:12:00,697 --> 01:12:02,274
Next to her breast.

774
01:12:02,323 --> 01:12:04,232
Is she pretty?

775
01:12:04,283 --> 01:12:06,241
Not bad.

776
01:12:07,286 --> 01:12:09,326
- Beautiful.
- No, pretty.

777
01:12:09,372 --> 01:12:10,700
- Beautiful.
- Pretty.

778
01:12:10,748 --> 01:12:14,580
- What does she want from you?
- She's broke.

779
01:12:14,627 --> 01:12:17,332
She wants a reward for the album.

780
01:12:17,380 --> 01:12:19,669
Or she collects photos, too.

781
01:12:19,716 --> 01:12:24,010
She wants to trade us
for a one-eyed man with glasses!

782
01:12:28,683 --> 01:12:29,714
No, you dope!

783
01:12:31,269 --> 01:12:33,641
She's in love.

784
01:12:33,688 --> 01:12:36,439
- I don't even know her.
- Yes, you do.

785
01:12:36,482 --> 01:12:38,309
Since when?

786
01:12:38,359 --> 01:12:40,103
You've always known her.

787
01:12:40,153 --> 01:12:41,433
In your dreams.

788
01:12:54,375 --> 01:12:55,953
Hello?

789
01:12:56,002 --> 01:13:00,082
Yes. You! Man with the plastic bag! It's for you.

790
01:13:01,633 --> 01:13:03,092
- Me?
- Yes.

791
01:13:06,429 --> 01:13:07,460
Thank you.

792
01:13:09,432 --> 01:13:10,463
Hello?

793
01:13:10,516 --> 01:13:13,268
Follow the blue arrows, Mr. Quincampoix.

794
01:14:38,563 --> 01:14:43,024
When the finger's pointing to the sky,
only a fool looks at the finger.

795
01:15:55,556 --> 01:15:56,588
Hello?

796
01:15:57,642 --> 01:15:59,967
I know the stranger in the pictures.

797
01:16:00,019 --> 01:16:04,100
He's a ghost. He's invisible, Mr. Quincampoix.

798
01:16:04,149 --> 01:16:07,518
He only appears when the film is developed.

799
01:16:07,569 --> 01:16:10,938
When a girl has her photo taken,

800
01:16:10,989 --> 01:16:16,943
he goes "Oooh!" in her ear,
while he gently caresses her neck.

801
01:16:16,995 --> 01:16:19,568
That's how he got caught, Mr. Quincampoix.

802
01:16:23,292 --> 01:16:24,574
Who are you?

803
01:16:24,628 --> 01:16:26,087
Page 51.

804
01:16:34,679 --> 01:16:36,257
[DO YOU

805
01:16:36,306 --> 01:16:38,132
WANT

806
01:16:38,182 --> 01:16:40,638
TO MEET ME?]

807
01:18:18,659 --> 01:18:21,494
Listen to this. "A boy of six,

808
01:18:21,536 --> 01:18:23,695
while his parents sleep, drives off

809
01:18:23,747 --> 01:18:25,490
in a pedal car.

810
01:18:25,540 --> 01:18:29,241
Found on a motorway
near Münster in Germany,

811
01:18:29,294 --> 01:18:32,876
he told the police he wanted to see the stars."

812
01:18:32,922 --> 01:18:36,587
Isn't life beautiful, eh?

813
01:18:36,634 --> 01:18:41,213
Love. The only bug she hadn't caught!

814
01:18:41,265 --> 01:18:44,301
- Nobody's immune.
- At least it gives me a break.

815
01:18:44,351 --> 01:18:46,557
Love's a great beautician.

816
01:18:48,772 --> 01:18:52,223
What's she like? Tall? Small? Blonde? Dark?

817
01:18:54,652 --> 01:18:56,728
Let's say... average height.

818
01:18:57,989 --> 01:19:01,026
Not a dwarf or a giraffe. Normal.

819
01:19:02,411 --> 01:19:04,652
Pretty, for her type.

820
01:19:04,705 --> 01:19:07,030
As for blonde or dark...

821
01:19:08,625 --> 01:19:11,709
...it's hard to say, but she wasn't a redhead.

822
01:19:11,753 --> 01:19:13,627
- Unless...
- Forget it.

823
01:19:14,756 --> 01:19:19,631
I do remember she casually asked
if you had a girlfriend.

824
01:19:19,677 --> 01:19:20,708
And?

825
01:19:20,762 --> 01:19:23,218
I said you weren't interested, right?

826
01:19:24,641 --> 01:19:26,136
You didn't!

827
01:19:26,185 --> 01:19:28,426
What do you care? You don't even know her.

828
01:19:29,479 --> 01:19:33,691
- Exactly. It's the mystery.
- You won't find mystery here.

829
01:19:33,733 --> 01:19:35,940
A pound of nectarines, please.

830
01:19:35,986 --> 01:19:38,821
These ones here are the prettiest.

831
01:19:38,863 --> 01:19:40,986
Trust him. He's an artist!

832
01:19:41,032 --> 01:19:44,116
He's been going home every night
with tons of unsold stock.

833
01:19:44,160 --> 01:19:47,328
What for? Is he stewing a pig?

834
01:19:47,372 --> 01:19:49,531
No, sir! He's studying art!

835
01:19:49,583 --> 01:19:53,283
He sells leeks all day long
and paints turnips all night!

836
01:19:53,336 --> 01:19:55,412
The boy's a useless vegetable.

837
01:19:55,464 --> 01:19:56,958
A good prompter

838
01:19:57,007 --> 01:20:00,589
in each cellar window
whispering cutting retorts

839
01:20:00,635 --> 01:20:03,256
would mean shy people had the last laugh.

840
01:20:03,304 --> 01:20:05,760
At least you'll never be a vegetable.

841
01:20:05,807 --> 01:20:08,049
Even artichokes

842
01:20:08,102 --> 01:20:09,133
have hearts.

843
01:20:12,147 --> 01:20:15,765
You'll never be a vegetable.
Even artichokes have hearts!

844
01:20:57,192 --> 01:20:58,817
Memory seven.

845
01:21:16,503 --> 01:21:20,750
Darling Mado,
I miss you more and more each day.

846
01:21:20,799 --> 01:21:24,085
I'm an exile in a world of dreary khaki.

847
01:21:24,136 --> 01:21:26,424
I can't sleep, can't eat...

848
01:21:26,471 --> 01:21:29,176
This camp was the biggest mistake of my life,

849
01:21:29,224 --> 01:21:33,008
depriving me of my beloved
for five long weeks.

850
01:21:33,061 --> 01:21:35,931
I think of you endlessly. Your Adrien.

851
01:21:37,690 --> 01:21:42,483
I turned down my last month's wages
instead of giving notice.

852
01:21:43,530 --> 01:21:46,864
I dream of better times ahead.

853
01:21:46,908 --> 01:21:50,906
An orange-coloured day. Remember, my love?

854
01:21:50,954 --> 01:21:53,030
Your ever-loving Adrien.

855
01:21:54,833 --> 01:21:56,243
Good news, darling Mado.

856
01:21:56,292 --> 01:21:59,626
Soon I'll be able to afford a car

857
01:21:59,671 --> 01:22:02,163
and drive home every night.

858
01:22:02,216 --> 01:22:06,628
Till then, meet me on Friday and we'll go out.

859
01:24:53,595 --> 01:24:55,801
[MOTHER]

860
01:24:58,642 --> 01:25:00,718
Psychiatric Helpline.

861
01:25:02,271 --> 01:25:04,347
Hello? Hello?

862
01:25:33,093 --> 01:25:35,549
[WHERE & WHEN?]

863
01:25:45,272 --> 01:25:47,728
One hour later at 11 Boulevard St Martin,

864
01:25:47,775 --> 01:25:51,393
Amélie walks into a party goods
and costume shop.

865
01:25:52,446 --> 01:25:56,907
At the same time,
a man leaves his home at 108 Rue Lecourbe.

866
01:25:58,869 --> 01:26:02,617
26 minutes later, Amélie is at the photo booth
at the Gare de I'Est.

867
01:26:06,876 --> 01:26:10,957
Simultaneously,
the man in red shoes parks outside.

868
01:26:11,006 --> 01:26:14,375
The time is exactly 11:40.

869
01:27:00,014 --> 01:27:02,090
At this precise moment,

870
01:27:02,141 --> 01:27:06,886
only Amélie has the key
to the riddle of the mystery man.

871
01:27:11,775 --> 01:27:13,483
How's it going, Mrs. Wells?

872
01:27:13,527 --> 01:27:16,363
It's always better when it's not raining.

873
01:27:16,405 --> 01:27:18,861
- This is for you.
- Me?

874
01:27:28,792 --> 01:27:32,493
Dear Mrs. Wells,
We recently recovered a mailbag

875
01:27:32,546 --> 01:27:34,622
that was lost in a plane crash

876
01:27:34,673 --> 01:27:38,339
on October 12th 1969 on Mont Blanc.

877
01:27:38,386 --> 01:27:42,846
We are forwarding the enclosed letter
to your address.

878
01:27:42,890 --> 01:27:47,053
Please accept our apologies
for the uncustomary delay.

879
01:27:47,102 --> 01:27:49,807
Jacques Grosjean, Customer Services.

880
01:27:51,148 --> 01:27:55,442
Darling Mado, I'm in exile.
I can't sleep, can't eat.

881
01:27:55,485 --> 01:27:57,229
I think of you endlessly.

882
01:27:57,279 --> 01:28:01,147
I know I've made
the biggest mistake of my life.

883
01:28:01,200 --> 01:28:03,905
I turned down that woman's money.

884
01:28:03,953 --> 01:28:08,911
If all goes well,
I'll soon be able to afford a house.

885
01:28:08,958 --> 01:28:11,994
I dream of better times ahead

886
01:28:12,044 --> 01:28:15,911
when you'll forgive me and join me here

887
01:28:15,964 --> 01:28:19,333
one orange-coloured day.
Your ever-loving Adrien.

888
01:28:49,165 --> 01:28:51,323
Mr. Dufayel, another package for you.

889
01:29:01,134 --> 01:29:04,384
Mr. Dufayel, do you know
what happened to the concierge?

890
01:29:05,806 --> 01:29:07,135
She got a letter.

891
01:29:08,184 --> 01:29:11,019
From her husband. 40 years late.

892
01:29:13,356 --> 01:29:15,431
That's a lot, isn't it, Mr. Dufayel?

893
01:29:28,662 --> 01:29:32,114
I'm not big on still life, Mr. Dufayel.

894
01:29:32,166 --> 01:29:35,167
Then work on your thin layer.

895
01:29:35,211 --> 01:29:37,962
Fat over thin. Always!

896
01:29:56,816 --> 01:29:58,607
- Mr. Dufayel...
- Yes!

897
01:29:58,651 --> 01:30:03,028
The papers said
that there'll soon be a new star.

898
01:30:03,072 --> 01:30:10,201
- So you're into stars now?
- I saw it on TV at my mum's, that's why.

899
01:30:12,039 --> 01:30:13,782
I don't know if it's true.

900
01:30:13,832 --> 01:30:16,158
In America

901
01:30:16,210 --> 01:30:19,496
they're going to take all the rich people's ashes,

902
01:30:19,547 --> 01:30:22,216
put them in a satellite

903
01:30:22,258 --> 01:30:24,583
and shoot it into space.

904
01:30:24,635 --> 01:30:27,007
The satellite's going to shine for ever.

905
01:30:31,642 --> 01:30:33,184
And Lady Di...

906
01:30:33,227 --> 01:30:35,468
Will they do the same for her?

907
01:30:35,520 --> 01:30:36,552
Lady Di, Lady Di!

908
01:30:36,606 --> 01:30:37,851
Give it a rest!

909
01:30:37,899 --> 01:30:40,650
I can't concentrate.

910
01:30:42,820 --> 01:30:43,851
Lady Di!

911
01:30:44,947 --> 01:30:45,978
Lady Di!

912
01:30:47,199 --> 01:30:48,230
Renoir.

913
01:32:29,552 --> 01:32:30,583
Morning, sir.

914
01:32:47,319 --> 01:32:48,350
Cambodia.

915
01:32:53,952 --> 01:32:55,695
I don't understand.

916
01:32:55,745 --> 01:32:59,612
Brilliant! You couldn't have done better.

917
01:32:59,665 --> 01:33:02,868
- Did it work?
- It's getting there.

918
01:33:02,918 --> 01:33:05,836
Ask me again any time. The harm's done.

919
01:33:05,880 --> 01:33:09,545
- What do you mean?
- Everybody calls me Snow White!

920
01:34:15,282 --> 01:34:18,117
[The Two Windmills café from 4pm.]

921
01:34:24,626 --> 01:34:26,535
- Eva?
- Yes?

922
01:34:26,586 --> 01:34:30,334
Could you stand in for me at four?

923
01:34:30,381 --> 01:34:32,290
Again?

924
01:34:35,636 --> 01:34:37,095
Close the door!

925
01:34:39,265 --> 01:34:41,257
What's up with him?

926
01:34:41,308 --> 01:34:43,052
Is he sulking?

927
01:34:43,102 --> 01:34:46,685
- He thinks I smile too much.
- He'd rather you frowned?

928
01:34:46,731 --> 01:34:49,648
With other men, yes.

929
01:34:52,361 --> 01:34:56,774
Nino is late. Amélie can only think
of two possible explanations.

930
01:34:56,824 --> 01:34:58,900
Firstly, that he didn't find the photo.

931
01:35:00,744 --> 01:35:03,200
Secondly, before he could assemble it,

932
01:35:03,247 --> 01:35:07,542
a gang of bank robbers took him hostage.

933
01:35:07,585 --> 01:35:09,578
The cops gave chase.

934
01:35:09,629 --> 01:35:11,420
They got away,

935
01:35:11,464 --> 01:35:14,216
but he caused a crash.

936
01:35:14,258 --> 01:35:16,465
When he came to,

937
01:35:16,511 --> 01:35:18,170
he'd lost his memory,

938
01:35:20,056 --> 01:35:21,929
An ex-con picked him up,

939
01:35:21,974 --> 01:35:26,185
mistook him for a fugitive,
and shipped him to Istanbul.

940
01:35:27,146 --> 01:35:29,388
He met some Afghan raiders,

941
01:35:29,441 --> 01:35:33,023
who took him to steal
some Russian warheads.

942
01:35:36,656 --> 01:35:40,488
But their truck hit a mine
at the border with Tajikistan.

943
01:35:40,535 --> 01:35:46,039
He survived, took to the hills,
and became a Mujaheddin.

944
01:35:46,082 --> 01:35:49,035
Amélie refuses to get upset for a guy

945
01:35:49,084 --> 01:35:53,664
who'll eat borscht all his life
in a hat like a tea cosy.

946
01:36:12,900 --> 01:36:15,107
- What can I get you?
- A coffee, please.

947
01:36:16,196 --> 01:36:18,069
A coffee.

948
01:36:40,095 --> 01:36:41,553
Here's your coffee.

949
01:36:43,097 --> 01:36:44,129
Thank you.

950
01:37:07,830 --> 01:37:10,156
[Today's menu]

951
01:37:19,175 --> 01:37:20,633
He's understood.

952
01:37:20,676 --> 01:37:23,880
He's going to put his teaspoon down,

953
01:37:25,306 --> 01:37:28,889
dip his finger in the sugar,

954
01:37:33,648 --> 01:37:36,352
turn around slowly,

955
01:37:36,400 --> 01:37:38,476
and speak to me.

956
01:37:44,075 --> 01:37:46,068
Excuse me.

957
01:37:47,579 --> 01:37:48,824
Is this you?

958
01:37:55,294 --> 01:37:56,539
Yes, it's you.

959
01:38:17,233 --> 01:38:19,309
I'll take that.

960
01:38:21,737 --> 01:38:23,397
Another coffee?

961
01:38:23,447 --> 01:38:25,570
- No, thanks. I'm fine.
- OK.

962
01:38:46,137 --> 01:38:50,598
So it's this man here,
the one with his hand up?

963
01:38:51,852 --> 01:38:52,883
Yes.

964
01:38:55,230 --> 01:38:58,100
Is she in love with him?

965
01:39:00,902 --> 01:39:01,933
Yes.

966
01:39:03,863 --> 01:39:07,232
I think it's time she took a real risk.

967
01:39:07,283 --> 01:39:11,779
She might just do that.
She's devising a stratagem.

968
01:39:11,829 --> 01:39:15,495
She's fond of stratagems.

969
01:39:17,544 --> 01:39:18,575
Yes.

970
01:39:20,296 --> 01:39:22,419
In fact, she's cowardly.

971
01:39:23,800 --> 01:39:27,169
That's why I can't capture her look.

972
01:39:29,013 --> 01:39:34,517
Dufayel's attempts to meddle are intolerable!

973
01:39:37,022 --> 01:39:42,976
If Amélie chooses to live in a dream

974
01:39:43,028 --> 01:39:47,239
and remain an introverted young woman,

975
01:39:47,282 --> 01:39:51,943
she has an absolute right to mess up her life!

976
01:40:26,696 --> 01:40:28,440
What are you doing, Mr. Dufayel?

977
01:40:30,825 --> 01:40:32,948
Tell me, Lucien.

978
01:40:32,994 --> 01:40:37,869
For deliveries,
do you keep keys to all the apartments?

979
01:40:50,345 --> 01:40:54,212
One of your booths is out of order.

980
01:40:56,351 --> 01:40:58,889
It seems to be jammed.

981
01:41:00,021 --> 01:41:02,309
Gare de I'Est ticket hall.

982
01:41:05,151 --> 01:41:07,524
- Buy a video, get one free.
- No, thanks.

983
01:41:14,285 --> 01:41:15,945
Sam?

984
01:41:16,996 --> 01:41:18,028
Samantha?

985
01:41:21,376 --> 01:41:22,407
Samantha?

986
01:41:27,340 --> 01:41:29,250
Can you stand in for me at...

987
01:41:51,698 --> 01:41:55,363
Photo booth, Gare de I'Est ticket hall,
Tuesday 5pm.

988
01:41:55,410 --> 01:41:58,744
[Can you stand in for me this afternoon?]

989
01:43:09,985 --> 01:43:11,313
Almost done.

990
01:43:16,449 --> 01:43:20,495
The mystery man wasn't a ghost
or a man scared of ageing,

991
01:43:20,537 --> 01:43:22,613
but simply the repairman,

992
01:43:22,664 --> 01:43:25,120
a normal guy doing his job.

993
01:43:27,252 --> 01:43:28,912
Sorry.

994
01:44:14,549 --> 01:44:17,918
He keeps spying on me!
It's making me sick.

995
01:44:17,969 --> 01:44:21,385
4:05: Blatant female conspiracy.

996
01:44:22,432 --> 01:44:25,883
Gosh, you're tense, Georgette!

997
01:44:26,936 --> 01:44:28,479
Good luck. You'll need it.

998
01:44:33,902 --> 01:44:38,480
Excuse me. Did you put this in my pocket?

999
01:44:38,532 --> 01:44:41,947
- Yes, but I'm not the one...
- I know. Where is she?

1000
01:44:41,993 --> 01:44:43,535
She's at her father's.

1001
01:44:43,578 --> 01:44:48,999
It's awkward. I'd like to speak to you, but...
I finish work at six.

1002
01:44:49,042 --> 01:44:51,000
- Can you come back?
- OK.

1003
01:44:52,045 --> 01:44:53,125
See you later.

1004
01:44:53,172 --> 01:44:56,754
4:08: Docking scheduled.

1005
01:45:28,581 --> 01:45:33,243
The blond guy in a camel coat.
He's very absent-minded, too.

1006
01:45:33,294 --> 01:45:35,039
How come?

1007
01:45:36,090 --> 01:45:38,545
He came back three times the same afternoon.

1008
01:45:39,801 --> 01:45:41,082
1:12:

1009
01:45:41,136 --> 01:45:42,416
Camel coat.

1010
01:45:42,471 --> 01:45:43,716
2:50:

1011
01:45:43,764 --> 01:45:45,590
Camel coat.

1012
01:45:45,640 --> 01:45:47,847
- 4:17: Camel coat.
- Stop it!

1013
01:45:48,894 --> 01:45:52,097
My rash has come back! Look, Suzanne!

1014
01:45:52,147 --> 01:45:55,847
My rash is back. He's driving me nuts.

1015
01:45:55,900 --> 01:45:58,060
Lay off!

1016
01:45:58,112 --> 01:46:02,405
If she had a clear conscience,
she wouldn't be in such a state.

1017
01:46:02,449 --> 01:46:04,406
I've had it. I'm going home.

1018
01:46:04,451 --> 01:46:07,950
Psychos are the last straw!

1019
01:46:09,331 --> 01:46:11,370
Georgette! Georg...

1020
01:46:12,959 --> 01:46:15,711
Stop smothering them!
Women need to breathe.

1021
01:46:15,754 --> 01:46:19,039
You let them breathe,
they want a change of air.

1022
01:46:19,090 --> 01:46:20,965
Fresh air's healthy.

1023
01:46:21,010 --> 01:46:23,002
Shut it, failure!

1024
01:46:25,556 --> 01:46:27,263
Failed writer, failed life...

1025
01:46:27,307 --> 01:46:29,881
I love the word "fail".

1026
01:46:29,935 --> 01:46:31,974
Failure is human destiny.

1027
01:46:32,020 --> 01:46:33,598
It's gasbag time!

1028
01:46:33,647 --> 01:46:36,897
Failure teaches us that life is but a draft,

1029
01:46:36,941 --> 01:46:40,809
a long rehearsal for a show that will never play.

1030
01:46:42,239 --> 01:46:44,564
I bet he stole that.

1031
01:46:44,617 --> 01:46:47,107
I do have some original ideas,

1032
01:46:47,161 --> 01:46:52,617
but people always steal them.
A bit like your women.

1033
01:46:52,666 --> 01:46:54,705
Meaning?

1034
01:46:54,751 --> 01:46:57,954
Meaning you'd better get used to it.

1035
01:46:58,004 --> 01:47:00,542
Speak for yourself, you...

1036
01:47:00,590 --> 01:47:01,621
What?

1037
01:47:05,387 --> 01:47:08,507
- What's going on?
- Nothing much. Georgette went out.

1038
01:47:08,557 --> 01:47:10,300
Joseph got mad.

1039
01:47:10,350 --> 01:47:11,845
"Went out?"

1040
01:47:11,894 --> 01:47:17,101
Just like Gina. You know who's she's with?
The guy with the plastic bag.

1041
01:47:18,817 --> 01:47:21,189
I saw their little game.

1042
01:47:21,236 --> 01:47:23,561
The note in the coat pocket,

1043
01:47:23,613 --> 01:47:25,238
4:08.

1044
01:47:25,281 --> 01:47:29,232
Back he comes, and hey presto!
Out they go.

1045
01:47:33,165 --> 01:47:36,830
- I'm worried for Amélie because I like you.
- What do you mean?

1046
01:47:37,878 --> 01:47:41,662
By and large, the men I like
are mentally unsound.

1047
01:47:41,715 --> 01:47:44,751
- I'd like to know more about you.
- Ask me questions.

1048
01:47:47,554 --> 01:47:49,346
One swallow doesn't make...?

1049
01:47:50,432 --> 01:47:51,464
A swallow?

1050
01:47:53,060 --> 01:47:54,602
A summer.

1051
01:47:54,645 --> 01:47:56,020
And clothes...?

1052
01:47:56,063 --> 01:47:57,605
The man.

1053
01:47:57,648 --> 01:47:59,058
- A good cat deserves...?
- A rat.

1054
01:47:59,107 --> 01:48:00,767
- Patience...?
- Is a virtue.

1055
01:48:00,817 --> 01:48:02,395
- Rolling stone...?
- Gathers no moss.

1056
01:48:02,444 --> 01:48:04,769
- It's a sin...?
- To steal a pin.

1057
01:48:04,821 --> 01:48:06,814
Absence makes...?

1058
01:48:06,865 --> 01:48:08,324
The heart grow fonder.

1059
01:48:08,366 --> 01:48:10,359
- Not bad.
- You collect them?

1060
01:48:10,410 --> 01:48:14,740
In my family, we say a man
who knows his proverbs can't be all bad.

1061
01:48:19,336 --> 01:48:22,787
Pretty girl from the 5th floor, listen to this!

1062
01:48:22,839 --> 01:48:25,793
- Do you believe in miracles?
- Not today.

1063
01:48:27,219 --> 01:48:29,377
You're in for a surprise.

1064
01:48:29,429 --> 01:48:32,762
What if I told you that a team of climbers

1065
01:48:32,807 --> 01:48:36,758
on Mont Blanc had found

1066
01:48:36,812 --> 01:48:41,438
hard proof that my husband loved me?

1067
01:49:14,808 --> 01:49:16,931
Lucien, I need some yeast.

1068
01:49:16,977 --> 01:49:20,892
For Miss Amélie?
She's baking her famous plum cake?

1069
01:49:20,940 --> 01:49:23,894
Collignon! Go and get the yeast.

1070
01:50:18,080 --> 01:50:19,704
Amélie?

1071
01:50:19,748 --> 01:50:20,779
Amélie?

1072
01:50:28,132 --> 01:50:29,163
Amélie?

1073
01:50:51,030 --> 01:50:52,061
[I'll be back]

1074
01:51:23,145 --> 01:51:26,146
Go into the bedroom, Miss Poulain.

1075
01:51:42,206 --> 01:51:45,325
So, little Amélie,

1076
01:51:45,376 --> 01:51:49,455
your bones aren't made of glass.

1077
01:51:49,504 --> 01:51:52,624
You can take life's knocks.

1078
01:51:52,674 --> 01:51:57,052
If you let this chance go by,

1079
01:51:57,096 --> 01:52:03,763
eventually your heart will become

1080
01:52:03,811 --> 01:52:09,849
as dry and brittle as my skeleton.

1081
01:52:11,485 --> 01:52:13,027
So...

1082
01:52:13,070 --> 01:52:16,236
Go and get him, for pete's sake!

1083
01:55:03,741 --> 01:55:09,577
[Without you, today's emotions
would be the scurf of yesterday's]

1084
01:56:05,887 --> 01:56:07,595
International airport.

1085
01:56:07,638 --> 01:56:12,680
September 28th 1997. It is exactly 11am.

1086
01:56:12,727 --> 01:56:15,431
At the funfair, near the ghost train,

1087
01:56:15,479 --> 01:56:18,646
the marshmallow twister is twisting.

1088
01:56:18,691 --> 01:56:20,979
Meanwhile, on a bench in Villette Square,

1089
01:56:21,026 --> 01:56:26,483
Félix Lerbier learns there are more links
in his brain than atoms in the universe.

1090
01:56:27,575 --> 01:56:28,690
Meanwhile,

1091
01:56:28,743 --> 01:56:32,408
at the Sacré Cœur,
the nuns are practising their backhand.

1092
01:56:32,455 --> 01:56:34,862
The temperature is 24°C,

1093
01:56:34,916 --> 01:56:36,789
humidity 70%,

1094
01:56:36,834 --> 01:56:40,084
atmospheric pressure 999 millibars.

